<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGOLAN REBELS CUT POWER TO CAPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The capital of Angola struggled with a blackout and scarce water Monday after 
the first major rebel offensive near Luanda in more than a year cut the city's 
power supply. 
</P>
<P>
 The attack southeast of Luanda, along with increased fighting elsewhere in the 
southern African nation, came as peace talks appeared at a standstill in 
Lusaka, Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
