<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION : PORT HUENEME; MAN ACCUSED OF SHOOTING AT WIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 33-year-old Port Hueneme man has been arrested on suspicion of firing a 
bullet at his wife, with the round entering an adjacent apartment and narrowly 
missing a neighbor, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 11:30 p.m. Sunday as John Tran and his wife, Qin 
Chen, 24, were arguing loudly in their apartment on Madera Circle, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 During the argument, police said Tran pulled out a .38-caliber handgun and 
fired one shot that missed Chen by two feet. The bullet then passed through a 
wall and into the apartment of 39-year-old Richard Garza next door, police 
said. The bullet missed Garza, who was standing at a sink. 
</P>
<P>
 Tran was taken into custody by police and booked into Ventura County Jail on 
suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon. He was released Monday on $5,000 
bail. He is scheduled to be arraigned Friday in Ventura County Municipal Court. 
JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
