<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION : OXNARD; CANDIDATES SOUGHT FOR ECONOMIC BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Candidates are being sought to fill two openings on the board of directors of 
the newly formed Greater Oxnard Economic Development Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members are responsible for helping develop a long-range plan to guide 
the corporation, formed earlier this year to lure new businesses and beef up 
Oxnard's economic base. 
</P>
<P>
 Already, the economic development corporation can claim partial credit for 
persuading GTE California to move to Oxnard. Due in part to a longstanding push 
to lure new businesses, the Thousand Oaks-based telephone company announced 
last month that it will establish a customer service center in Oxnard, a move 
that will bring 650 jobs to the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The board is scheduled to expand from seven to nine members in a few months, 
and prospective board members should be prepared to actively govern the 
fledgling corporation and help support its mission. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in applying should contact corporation President Steve Kinney 
at 385-7444 or write: Greater Oxnard Economic Development Corp., 711 S. A St., 
Oxnard, 93030. FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
