<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIVER APPRECIATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thanks for the excellent two-piece feature on the Ventura River by Joanna 
Miller. The articles are a fine example of diligent journalism.Despite keeping 
in close personal touch with the Ventura River situation, I still learned new 
details from Miller's reporting. 
</P>
<P>
 It is hoped that her articles and the efforts of local environmental groups 
will result in a major shift in the city of Ventura's thinking about the 
Ventura River. In this time of heightened ecological awareness, it is 
remarkable that city officials do not see the river first and foremost as a 
valuable feature that could add greatly to the local quality of life, if 
managed in an enlightened way. 
</P>
<P>
 LLOYD F. KIFF 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo 
</P>
<P>
 Lloyd Kiff is director of the Western Foundation of Vertebrate Zoology.  
</P>
