<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANGEROUS CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding the freeway police chase of March 29, I find it incredible that 
three police agencies were involved in apprehending a suspect with three 
warrants for drug possession and a no-show in court. 
</P>
<P>
 They created an extreme danger to the public during heavy morning traffic 
hours, just to have some fun. Knowing that the suspect was not an armed ax 
murderer, they should not have pursued. They could have arrested him later in a 
more safe manner. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, why cannot the police take the car keys from stopped drivers, until they 
finish running the records check? 
</P>
<P>
 TONY MARIS 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Village 
