<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILDLIFE PRIORITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The article on March 16, "The Fur Flies," illustrated beautifully the 
difference between a mountain and a molehill.Surely, the people who are 
complaining about the squirrels must have realized that living in Wildwood 
would place them smack in the middle of what makes Thousand Oaks such a grand 
place: wildlife right outside one's door. 
</P>
<P>
 When those folks get tired of the molehill (a.k.a. squirrels), show 'em to the 
mountain so they can tackle some real problems like gangs, drive-by shootings 
and drunk driving. 
</P>
<P>
 As for me, I'll take the squirrels and coyotes and hawks and possums and all 
that crawls and slithers any day over those other problems. 
</P>
<P>
 JOAN DOWNEY 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
