<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISLEADING PHOTO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your coverage of "Owner of Dog Killed by Police Files Claim" (March 31) is an 
example of sensationalism that I am disappointed to see in your paper. 
</P>
<P>
 When I first saw the picture on B1 of a helpless puppy, I was led to believe 
that was the dog shot by police. Further reading of the story revealed that the 
owners had lost their pit bull, not a puppy. While all pit bulls may not fit 
the vicious stereotype, the picture was very misleading. 
</P>
<P>
