<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; LEMIEUX EJECTED IN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tom Barrasso made 26 saves and the Pittsburgh Penguins survived Mario 
Lemieux's first-period ejection and beat the Tampa Bay Lightning, 2-1, at 
Pittsburgh on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lemieux was given a game misconduct penalty for the third time in his career 
after he left the penalty box to charge referee Kerry Fraser.Lemieux was 
disputing a high-sticking call. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaromir Jagr and Tomas Sandstrom scored for Pittsburgh as Barrasso continued a 
hot streak in which he has gone 13-6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 N.Y. Rangers 3, Florida 2 -- Sergei Nemchinov and Steve Larmer scored 
third-period goals and goalie Mike Richter outdueled John Vanbiesbrouck at New 
York. 
</P>
<P>
 Quebec 6, Buffalo 4 -- Mike Ricci's two power-play goals highlighted a 
three-goal outburst in the first 61 seconds of the second period at Quebec. 
</P>
<P>
 Philadelphia 2, Winnipeg 2 -- The Flyers' Kevin Dineen beat Tim Cheveldae in 
the crease with 85 seconds remaining to get the tie. 
</P>
</TEXT>
