<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING BRIEFING: A NIGHT WHEN 76ERS' DEFENSE PARTED QUICKER THAN RED SEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 From Keith Groller of the Allentown (Pa.) Morning Call:  
</P>
<P>
 "On a religious holiday and a night that the classic film 'Ten Commandments' 
was shown on television, it was kind of appropriate that 76er fans were 
chanting 'Moses! Moses! Moses!' Sunday night at Philadelphia's Spectrum. 
</P>
<P>
 "Moses Malone, the player the fans were calling for, never played. Neither did 
most of the Sixers, although they did get on the court." 
</P>
<P>
 The Boston Celtics routed Philadelphia, 135-112. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Trivia time: Who holds the NBA record for most rebounds in a game? 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Green pastures: Michael Jordan, on being assigned to the double-A Birmingham 
Barons of the Southern League: 
</P>
<P>
 "I think my skills are at that level. Plus, Birmingham has some nice golf 
courses." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Quiz: Columnist Bernie Lincicome of the Chicago Tribune offers this baseball 
test: 
</P>
