 Entering last week, Fountain Valley wasn't receiving much notice in the Sunset 
League softball race. Thanks in large part to Collins, that has changed. 
Wednesday, she had two hits, including a three-run home run, and drove in four 
runs in the Oilers' 7-1 victory over Marina, then the top-ranked team in the 
county. Friday, she hit a home run in a 1-0 victory over then-No. 6 Huntington 
