<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOFTBALL; UNBEATEN UPLAND BEATS MATER DEI IN TITLE GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The fifth time's a charm. 
</P>
<P>
 Free-swinging Upland High won the Woodbridge Classic Monday at Harvard Park in 
Irvine, scoring a 2-1 victory over Mater Dei in the championship game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders (12-0) teased Mater Dei (10-3) before scoring two runs in the 
bottom of the sixth inning and winning the tournament for the first time in the 
five years they've attended. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a good tournament," said Upland Coach Ed Ulloa, who lives in Irvine. 
"We like coming here." 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders beat three of Orange County's top 10 teams to win the title: 
Fifth-ranked Kennedy in the quarterfinals, ninth-ranked Foothill in the 
semifinals and eighth-ranked Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
 They won the final because tournament most valuable player Kelly Smith (10-0, 
0.10 earned-run average) gave up five hits, facing only two over the minimum in 
the final six innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei scored in the first. Lisa Tully got the first of her two singles, 
took second on a sacrifice bunt, reached third on Candace Kollen's single and 
scored on Margaret Hollis' grounder to shortstop. 
</P>
<P>
 Kollen's hit gave her nine in her previous 10 at-bats; she had four hits, five 
steals and three runs batted in in an 11-2 victory over Woodbridge in the 
semifinal, a game played earlier in the day; it was suspended Saturday after 
two Warriors were injured and taken to the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Monarch pitcher Patty Godwin (10-2), who pitched five innings in Monday's 
portion of the semifinal, battled fatigue and a blister on the index finger of 
her pitching hand. Upland hit her hard from the fourth inning on -- and scored 
in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Monica Loya doubled and Christy Sears was hit by a pitch. A double steal and a 
passed ball on a walk scored Loya, tying the score 1-1. With runners at second 
and third, Shanna Humphries' grounder to shortstop scored Sears with the 
deciding run. 
</P>
<P>
 In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 7, Woodbridge 0 -- Marie Gieron gave up seven hits for Foothill 
(11-5) in the third-place game. Woodbridge is 13-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 2, Bellflower 1 -- Lisa Pitt pitched a one-hitter as Kennedy (10-3) 
took fifth place. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 2, Lakewood 0 -- Misty Lauby pitched a two-hitter and struck out 13 
for El Toro (8-4) in the consolation championship. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 5, Santa Ana Valley 4 -- Magnolia (7-5) won in the bottom of the 
seventh inning when Shannon Carlson tripled and scored when Santa Ana Valley 
overthrew the catcher. Jannell Hanstein also had a two-run double for the 
Sentinels. 
</P>
