<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THOMAS S. MULLIGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Politics: A 26-year-old state legislator from Providence, R.I., is winning 
strong support from Hollywood in his campaign for Congress.MCA Chairman Lew R. 
Wasserman's fund-raiser for the young politician attracted contributions from 
QVC chief Barry Diller, Motown Records Chairman Clarence Avant, MCA President 
Sidney J. Sheinberg and other luminaries, the Providence Journal-Bulletin 
reported. Non-industry backers include real estate baron and San Francisco 
Giants owner Walter Shorenstein, professional golfer Amy Alcott and Los Angeles 
gay activist David Mixner. The source of the youthful Rhode Islander's appeal? 
Hollywood tends to favor liberal causes, so perhaps it's that candidate Patrick 
Kennedy is a left-leaning Democrat, much like his father, Sen. Edward M. 
Kennedy (D-Mass.). THOMAS S. MULLIGAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
