<P>
 A 19-year-old Pierce College student faces rape charges for allegedly holding 
his ex-girlfriend against her will for three days, raping her repeatedly and 
beating her so severely with a pipe that patches of her skin came off, 
authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Lim of Woodland Hills was arrested at a supermarket Sunday night after 
he started hitting the woman in front of witnesses, Los Angeles Police Lt. 
George Rock said. 
</P>
<P>
 Several onlookers subdued Lim and held him for police, Rock said. The 
23-year-old woman was taken to a hospital, where it was discovered that she was 
severely bruised from the waist down. 
