<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; REPEAT SEX OFFENDER GETS 78-YEAR TERM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By -- THOM MROZEK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A North Hollywood man convicted of repeatedly raping a woman while he was on 
parole in another sex case was sentenced Monday to 78 years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Lawrence Vernon Jones, 27, was convicted of 12 felony counts in the Sept. 11 
assault of a 23-year-old woman near Magnolia and Cahuenga boulevards in North 
Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 When Jones confronted the woman, who was walking alone to a store to purchase 
cigarettes just after midnight, she attempted to defend herself with a rock, 
according to testimony at the trial. But Jones disarmed her and used the rock 
to beat her. The woman testified that Jones also choked her. 
</P>
<P>
 "During the course of the next four hours, he terrorized her," Deputy Dist. 
Atty. Kathleen M. Cady wrote in a sentencing memorandum. "He raped her at least 
three times and sodomized her at least three times." 
</P>
<P>
 In sentencing Jones, Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Sandy Kriegler said he used 
"a high degree of cruelty." 
</P>
<P>
 Jones was on parole after being convicted in 1988 of assault with the intent 
to commit rape. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones was arrested four days after the attack, when the victim saw him walking 
down a street. -- THOM MROZEK 
</P>
</TEXT>
