<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: KAY MAINTAINS THE LARGEST WAR CHEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newcomer Arthur Kay has the largest campaign fund of the eight candidates for 
San Fernando City Council, reporting $36,720 in contributions received, 
according to the most recent financial disclosure statements for the upcoming 
April 12 election. 
</P>
<P>
 Kay's fund -- $34,000 of which comes from his own law firm -- amounts to about 
$6 for every registered voter in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Incumbent Doude Wysbeek has the second largest war chest, with $22,899, and 
newcomer Raul Godinez had the third largest campaign fund, with $9,024. Dan 
Acuna reported a fund of $4,700, Jose Hernandez $4,044 fund and Joanne 
Baltierrez $3,035. John Becker had a fund of $0. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez's statement was stamped received on Monday, three days past the 
March 31 deadline. City Clerk Wilma Miller confirmed that the statement was 
filed late. She said that candidate Ed Guzman had still not submitted his 
statement by Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The statements cover the period from Feb. 27 to March 26, and include the 
previous statement, from Jan. 1 to Feb. 26. The final statements, which cover 
from March 27 to June 30, are due July 31. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
