<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; 'TASTE' FUND-RAISER TO BE HELD SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The junior auxiliary of the Assistance League of Fullerton will hold its 15th 
annual "Taste of the Town" fund-raiser Sunday at the Brea Mall to raise money 
for needy children who cannot afford dental care. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will take place from 7 to 10 p.m. More than 800 people are expected 
to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 About 25 local restaurants, including Ye Olde Wood Ship of Fullerton, Bella 
Caffe of Brea and Portofino's of La Habra, will provide samples of their 
specialties. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost is $40, which covers "all the food, beer and wine you can consume," 
event officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from the event will benefit the Junior Auxiliary Dental Health 
Program, which pays for dental treatment for children. 
</P>
<P>
 The program was started in 1970, and more than 100 children received free 
dental services through the junior auxiliary last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The event's dress code will be cocktail attire. 
</P>
<P>
 For tickets or more information, call (714) 525-2990. MIMI KO 
</P>
