<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; POLICE SAY MAN POINTED GUN AT OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles police officer shot at but missed a man the officer said pointed 
a gun at him at an apartment complex in North Hollywood, authorities said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 9:15 p.m. Sunday when officers arrived at the 
complex in the 11900 block of Valerio Street in response to a complaint that 
two groups of men living there were fighting. 
</P>
<P>
 Mario Campirano, 20, ran and appeared to point a gun at Officer Luis Torres, 
who was chasing him, said Sgt. Robert Ontiveros of the Los Angeles Police 
Department's North Hollywood Division. Torres fired one shot from his 
9-millimeter pistol at Campirano but missed. 
</P>
<P>
 Campirano was arrested half a block away by other officers. Police said they 
retraced his path but could not find the gun. 
</P>
<P>
 Campirano was arrested on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon against a 
police officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Also arrested were Cory Webb, 26, on suspicion of shooting at Campirano, and 
Roger Coleman, 23, on suspicion of being a convicted felon in possession of a 
firearm, Ontiveros said. 
</P>
