<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND BOX OFFICE; BASEBALL FILM IN A LEAGUE OF ITS OWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID J. FOX 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Moviegoing took a dive on the Easter Sunday weekend and only one of the five 
new films attracted good, if not booming, business. That was "Major League II," 
from Warner Bros., starring Charlie Sheen.Opening to sluggish response were 
"Clifford," in seventh place, and "Thumbelina," in eighth. The other two 
debuting films didn't make the Top 10: The star-laden "The House of the 
Spirits" grossed $1.7 million and ranked 11th, and "Jimmy Hollywood," a film by 
Barry Levinson, took in only $1.5 million for 14th place. 
</P>
<P>
