<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: HOUSE OF FABRICS REPORTS SHARP DECLINE IN PROFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 House of Fabrics Inc., a Sherman Oaks-based chain of fabric stores, said its 
fiscal fourth-quarter profit fell sharply from a year earlier, partly because 
of $1 million in expenses due to the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 For the quarter ended Jan. 31, the company earned $212,000, down from $2.21 
million in the same period a year earlier.Revenue in the latest quarter 
declined 6%, to $147.6 million from $157.7 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's operating profit in the latest quarter was $4.12 million, but it 
incurred $3.1 million in interest expenses. Plus, the company was hurt by the 
earthquake, which damaged corporate headquarters and a number of its retail 
stores. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year ended Jan. 31, House of Fabrics reported a loss of $29.5 
million, contrasted with a profit of $5.2 million in its previous fiscal year. 
The loss included a charge of $12.9 million for restructuring. Revenue in the 
latest fiscal year totaled $546.7 million, down slightly from $557.5 million a 
year earlier. The company said its bank debt and inventory were down and that 
it would continue to close unproductive stores. 
</P>
