REGIONAL EARNINGS: OROAMERICA REPORTS 71% PROFIT BOOST FOR QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 OroAmerica Inc., a Burbank manufacturer and distributor of jewelry, said its 
fiscal fourth-quarter profit surged 71%, to $3.41 million from $2 million in 
the same quarter a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the three months ended Jan. 28, the company's revenue increased 3%, to 
$62.3 million from $60.5 million. The company attributed the strong earnings 
results to increased business with big retailers, such as Wal-Mart, and getting 
a better handle on its costs. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year ended Jan. 28, OroAmerica's profit doubled, to $8.2 
million from $4.02 million a year earlier. Revenue in the latest fiscal year 
totaled $203.4 million, up 16% from $176.1 million in its previous fiscal year. 
