<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INTERNATIONAL REMOTE POSTS RECORD PROFITS IN '93 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 International Remote Imaging Systems Inc., a Chatsworth-based manufacturer of 
clinical laboratory equipment, reported record profits and sales for its fourth 
quarter and for 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth quarter, the company's profit was $418,349, up 41% from $295,691 
for the same period a year earlier. Its revenue in the fourth quarter rose 13% 
to $2.67 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the fiscal year ending Dec. 31, the company posted a profit of $1.28 
million, up 66% from earnings of $772,377 in 1992. Last year's revenue totaled 
$9.63 million, a 20% increase from $8 million in fiscal 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed its profit surge to increased sales of instruments and 
to improved efficiency in its manufacturing and field service operations. 
</P>
