</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Incomnet Inc., a Woodland Hills telecommunications company, reported a 
fourth-quarter profit of $316,488, rebounding from a loss of $1.44 million in 
the same period a year earlier. Revenue for the quarter that ended Dec. 31 more 
than doubled to $5.07 million, from $2.31 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, the company posted a loss of $948,769 compared with a loss of 
$2.02 million for 1992. Incomnet said results in 1993 included restructuring 
charges of about $1.4 million for its subsidiary, National Telephone & 
Communications. 
</P>
