<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: AMGEN MOVES UP TO 304TH IN 1994 FORTUNE 500 LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County's only entry on the Fortune 500 list, Amgen Inc., moved up 22 
notches in the 1994 ranking of America's largest industrial corporations. 
</P>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks biotechnology concern placed 304th on this year's list, up 
from 326th in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 In sales, which determine a company's ranking, Amgen reported $1.306 billion 
last year, a 24% increase over 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 In other categories, the concern ranked 63rd in profits ($383.3 million), 
229th in assets ($1.765 billion) and fifth in profits as a percentage of sales 
(29.3%). 
</P>
<P>
 Amgen tops the entire list in return to investors over the past 10 years, with 
an average annual return of 45%. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, however, the company came in a dismal 410th in return to investors, 
with shareholders suffering a 29.9% loss in their stock. 
</P>
<P>
 That last point prompts Fortune to ask: "Is red-hot Amgen, tops in 10-year 
total return to investors, cooling off? Sales of Epogen, its market-leading 
kidney treatment, have begun to slow down." 
</P>
</TEXT>
