<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: DOLE TO CONSOLIDATE PART OF DIVISION INTO FRESNO PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dole Food Co., a Westlake Village-based food and real estate concern, said it 
will consolidate some of its dried-fruit operations into a plant it purchased 
near Fresno, part of a "strategic review" of the dried-fruit business. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of the consolidation, Dole expects that all of its consumer raisins 
now processed at its Kerman plant and prune processing now at a plant in Morgan 
Hill will be moved to the new Fresno facility starting in late fall.Dole said 
the move is intended to strengthen its position in consumer packaged goods and 
to lower costs. 
</P>
<P>
 Separately, Dole said it has formed an alliance with the New Zealand Kiwi 
Board to market fresh New Zealand kiwi in Japan. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the agreement, Dole will be the exclusive sales and distribution agent 
for New Zealand kiwi in 1994. Sales of New Zealand kiwi exported to Japan total 
about $130 million, Dole said. 
</P>
