<P>
 Councilman Irv Pickler, who suffered two broken legs in a recent car crash, 
said Monday that he expects to be released from Western Medical Center-Santa 
Ana by midweek and may be at next week's council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 "My strength is coming back," said Pickler, 72.He was injured March 26 when he 
his car slammed into a pole as he swerved to miss another that turned in front 
of him. 
</P>
