<TEXT>
<P>
 Nanny taxes -- The Social Security Administration must record taxes on wages 
for at least 40 quarters, which translates into 10 years, before a nanny can 
qualify to collect a retirement check. A March 28 editorial misstated the 
number of quarters during which an employer must pay taxes in order for a 
household worker to receive benefits. 
</P>
